The paper discusses a security vulnerability in real-time systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on real-time schedulers, which are commonly used in systems such as automotive, avionic, power plants, and industrial control systems, indicating that the paper may also fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and embedded systems (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the implementation of the ScheduLeak algorithm on real operating systems, indicating that it may also fall under the categories of operating systems (cs.OS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
